&lt;p&gt;There are two corollary bugs:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul class=&quot;alternate&quot; type=&quot;square&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Compiler converts field ids that are larger than max &lt;b&gt;int&lt;/b&gt; (i.e. &amp;gt; 2**31) to -1, and subsequently errors if there are multiple such fields.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;


&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;$ thrift --gen java big_field_ids.thrift
&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;-1: max33&quot;&lt;/span&gt; - field identifier/name has already been used
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;ul class=&quot;alternate&quot; type=&quot;square&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Compiler does error when a field id is too large for its internal representation (i.e. &amp;gt; 2**63)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;


&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;struct BigFieldIds {
